        .wimage However this form of artificial intelligence(AI) is limited by the number of rules taught; it can never surpass human intelligence as it cannot learn on its own. 
          br
          br
          |If given unfamiliar input it won't know what to do.
      span.iterim
        h2  The solution?
      .item
        div 
          h2 Machine learning
          | A field of computer science where a computer can learn without being explicitly programmed.

      .item
        div 
          | One form of machine learning is where the AI is trained/taught using a set of labelled inputs.
          br
          br
          | Essentially all machines are just trying to answer questions. By giving them enough example questions and answers they can learn how to produce the solutions. Like a child given a maths book with half the answers filled in.
      span.iterim
        h2  How can this be done?      
      .item
        img(src="images/brain.png")
        .wimage
          h2 Neural Networks
          | The brain is the most powerful, general purpose computer in existence, creating and storing all of a humans intelligence, memories and reasoning via billions of inter-connected neurons. 
          br 
          br
          | Neural networks are a structure used in machine learning inspired by this.
          br
          br
          | A group of connected node layers, each layer building on the knowledge of the previous.
      .item
        img(src="images/network.png")
        .wimage We don't need to know how to connect the nodes together as this is what the machine learns. For example it could learn that it doesn't make sense for hair length, to inform the nose size property.
      .item
        div The more data we give the machine, the more it can learn, the better it can answer a wider variety of questions. 
          br
          br
          |This is why companies collect huge amounts of data.       
      .item
        div 
          h2 Applications of Machine Learning
          |One key use of machine learning is computer vision, giving machines the ability to recognize shapes and patterns from raw pixel data, with numerous applications.
